(i) Polymer The factionalized GO and π-conjugated polymers composites have been explored as the switching layer in RRAM to achieve high ON/OFF current ratio, high stability, and lower switching voltage. For example, reference [, 106: #cpb_26_3_038501bib106] presented soluble triphenylamine-based polyazomethine (TPAPAM)-GO RRAM which shows low SET voltage and high stability. The RRAM structure is ITO/TPAPAM-GO/Al. Similar to the role of PCMO in PCMO-GO RRAM, the TPAPAM is used as the hole-transport agent due to its low ionization potential, high mobility, and excellent hole injection. This device shows reverse bipolar switching property. The SET voltage is ~ -1 V and the RESET voltage is near 2.2 ON/OFF current ratio can be over 103 at -1 V. The retention time is more than 104 s and the HRS/LRS resistance degrades little after 108 read cycles, which indicates TPAPAM, served as hole-transport agent, greatly improves the stability of GO RRAM.Although the high stability and low SET voltage are obtained in these RRAMs, the ON/OFF current ratio needs further improvement. Reference [, 116: #cpb_26_3_038501bib116] proposed Pt/rGO- thionine(th)/Pt RRAM and the layered rGO-th film flakes can be obtained by filtering the rGO-th solution and transfer to other substrate. The rGO film decorated by thionine owns a large resistance, which can be as high as 7×107 Ω in the OFF state. These features guarantee a relative high ON/OFF ratio. For this device, the ratio can reach up to 5×104 with the read voltage 0.1 V, improving near 50 times compared to TPAPAM-GO based RRAM. The switching mechanism is different from the ordinary filament forming and rupturing. It depends on whether the conductive path built by linking thionine molecules and further reduced GO between two electrodes is connected or disconnected. Similar to the filament, this conductive path is to transport charge with little hindrance and its connection or disconnection is determined by the external voltage, making the device show the HRS and LRS resistance switching behavior. The SET voltage varies from 1.91 V to 3.93 V, while the RESET one from -0.47 V to -1.04 V, which indicates that the conductive path is hard to form and easy to break down, needing high SET voltage and low RESET voltage. Moreover, this device also owns fast switching speed (< 5 ns) and long retention time (over 105 s). After 350 switching cycles, the resistances do not show obvious degradation, exhibiting good endurance and stability.Other GO-polymer composites are also used as the switching layer to improve GO RRAM properties. GO-PI based RRAM[, 117: #cpb_26_3_038501bib117] can achieve multilevel resistive switching owing to the trapping effect in GO-PI film. GO-polypyrrole (PPy)[, 118: #cpb_26_3_038501bib118] based RRAM realizes a high ON/OFF current ratio over 105 with good stability and solves the problem of the low ON/OFF current ratio for ordinary GO RRAM issue well

(ii) Nanoparticle GO-based memory decorated by nanoparticle, such as Au, can improve the memory switching property.[, 119: #cpb_26_3_038501bib119,, 120: #cpb_26_3_038501bib120] Reference [, 121: #cpb_26_3_038501bib121] presented a gold nanoparticle decorated rGO RRAM (Al/Au Nps-rGO-PVA/Pt) with polyvinyl alcohol (PVA) matrix. The Au decorated rGO sheet is synthesized by using the mixture of HAuCl4 solution (2.5 mM, 10 ml), GO flakes (20 mg), and aqueous PVA solution (1 wt.%, 50 ml). After 10 h stirring, a sodium borohydride solution (10 ml) is used to reduce the GO and Au3+ to rGO and Au NP to obtain the Au NPs-rGO-PVA film. Because this device is fabricated on the PET substrate, it owns high flexibility, which is very suitable for flexible circuit application. The Au NP acts as the filament linker between rGO sheets and helps lower the SET voltage (-0.44 V) compared to the control rGO RRAM (~ -5.6 V). For GO RRAM, the reduction and oxidation of GO under different voltage bias is the key to form or rupture conductive filament. The interfacial defects near Au NP can act as trapping sites and accelerate this process by the internal electrical field generated by these sites. Apart from that, the device owns a relatively high ON/OFF current ratio (> 103), larger than that of the control GO RRAM (~ 2.5 × 102). The relatively long retention time (> 104 s) shows the good endurance. But when the cycles are increased to some degree, the fluctuation of SET and RESET voltages becomes a little large.Other kinds of nanoparticles, such as Ni,[, 122: #cpb_26_3_038501bib122] are used to improve and change the RRAM behavior, showing the promising application in memory and neuromorphic field

(iii) 2D materials 2D materials are similar to π-conjugated polymers, which are layered, have a plane-like structure, and own many excellent electrical and optical properties.[, 123: #cpb_26_3_038501bib123-, 127: #cpb_26_3_038501bib127] GO decorated by 2D materials can also improve the switching property for RRAM. Reference [, 128: #cpb_26_3_038501bib128] used the MoS2-GO composite as the active layer to fabricate GO RRAM. Because MoS2 has larger conductivity than GO, the MoS2 component in the MoS2-GO film will increase the whole composite conductivity and facilitate oxygen migration in GO when the external voltage is applied. Therefore, low SET (~ -1.2 V) and RESET(~ 1.5 V) voltages can be obtained. But the ON/OFF current ratio (~ 102) is a bit small due to the low resistance in HRS
